<item>
            <title>[LU-18811] Open fname/fid at early stage in &apos;lfs migrate&apos; command</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18811</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Split from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15425&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lfs migrate&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;lfs_migrate&amp;quot; to accept list of FIDs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15425&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15425&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the discussion, it&apos;s better to open file(s) to be migrated at early stage when the pathname or fid is parsed from command line arguments/stdin/LIST_FILE. Then pass the fd down to various functions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some functions may be splitted into an internal function which accepts fd, and wrapper functions which open filename/fid and call the internal version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
